description:
Annie is one of the playable characters in League of Legends. She is the daughter of Gregori and Amoline. The couple quickly suspected that there was something special about their daughter. When she was two years old, Annie miraculously bewitched a shadow bear and turned it into her pet. To this day she keeps her bear ''Tibbers'' by her side, often keeping him spellbound as a stuffed doll to be carried like a child's toy. The combination of Annie's lineage and the dark magic of her birthplace have given this little girl tremendous arcane power.

Annie's parents, a Gray Warlock and a Shadow Witch, were leaders of an outcast society.
Together they led an exodus of magicians and other intelligentsia from Noxus, resettling their followers beyond the Great Barrier to the northern reaches of the unforgiving Voodoo Lands. Though survival was a challenge at times, the Gray Order's colony managed to thrive in a land where others would have died.
name: Annie
Pest Control Man / Galdys, his wife

description:
Sejuani is a playable character in League of Legends. As a child, the leader of the Winter's Claw watched her tribe die, one after one. She was the only one of her siblings that survived to become ten years old. Yet she feared for her life, sure that she would be the next to die. Becoming desperate, she sought spiritual counsel from the tribe's mystic. She told Sejuani that she one day would conquer and unite the tribes of the Freljord. However, the mystic left out the event of her death.

Now, when she had absolute faith in her destiny, Sejuani pushed herself to extremes and got hardened that way. She turned pain into power and hunger into an encouragement. She walked into blizzards without food or furs, challenged the strongest warriors, one after another until she became the leader. The tribe then grew stronger, even though she learned that being cold and unforgiving was the only way. 

A peace offering from Ashe's tribe insulted Sejuani greatly. Ashe told her that if they united the clans, the Winter's Claw would never go hungry again. Sejuani just simply hated the idea of getting that luxury, and started to despise Ashe's tribe. After telling her people that charity would bring only weakness, she burned the given supplies and sent the tribe back with one message:  the Winter's Claw would prove to the Avarosan that only the strong deserve to survive in the Freljord. After that event, Sejuani rode out with her warriors to inflict many painful lessons to others.
name: Sejuani
Rebecca Weston / Officer Gant (Venusian) / Security Officer (Odysseus)

description:
Julia is the wife of the main character Henry in the game Firewatch.

The couple met in a bar in Boulder, CO. They quickly hit it off, and soon afterwards, they are engaged, get married and get a dog. After the wedding, Julia gets a job request at Yale University in Connecticut, and it's up to the player if she takes the job or not. Sadly, it's soon revealed that she is suffering from Alzheimer's. Her condition quickly gets worse, and Henry sees how her family comes and gets Julia and takes her home to Australia. 

Her character is never seen in Firewatch. A lot is known about her thanks to Henry talking about her to his new job partner, Delilah. There's only one picture of Julia that we can see in the game, and it sits on Henry's desk at the Lookout Station. In the photo, her face is covered by a large camera. Julia's voice is briefly heard over the radio one night when Henry is delusional when being half-awake.
name: Julia

description:
Tommy, an Italian-American, is portrayed with a tall, swarthy, handsome appearance, combed dark brown, almost black hair, and a constant five o'clock shadow. He first appears wearing a light blue-green Hawaiian shirt with dark blue palm trees printed on it, a gold pearl necklace around his neck, a gold watch around his left wrist, and a pair of blue jeans and white sneakers. This outfit becomes known as Tommy’s "street" clothes. As the game progresses, Tommy is offered more wardrobe options: he obtains a blue-purple pastel suit with the sleeves rolled up over a black dress shirt and black loafers, as well as the option of a dark pinstripe suit labeled as "Mr. Vercetti" (which bears similarities to Tony Montana's uniform). A light green costume is available to perform a bank robbery, complete with a hockey mask, and is even able to wear the uniform for an allied gang, among many others.

Tommy Vercetti, in several ways, exhibits characteristics of fictional drug lord Tony Montana from the 1983 film Scarface. This coincides with the heavy themes and appearance of the movie that has been implemented into Vice City. Among these characteristics, his exile from his old home (Liberty City), his rise to power (acquiring property and wealth in the city, and a mansion which also sports an interior similar to that of Montana’s mansion). Tommy is also a hired assassin, has killed his own collaborators (Lance Vance), taken over his temporary boss’s business (Ricardo Diaz) and rebelled against his former leader (Sonny Forelli), as Tony Montana had. The only notable difference is that the final gunfight in Montana's mansion sees Montana eventually killed, whereas the final gunfight in Tommy's mansion sees Tommy managing to single-handedly take down his captors and survive.
name: Tommy Vercetti

description:
Dante is the primary protagonist of the Devil May Cry series created and published by Capcom. In the first four games, Dante is a private investigator and a demon hunting vigilante. He want to track down and kill those who murdered his mother and corrupted his brother. He is the son of Sparda who is a demon of great power. That's why Dante possesses numerous powers beyond that of any human. He can use a combination with a variety of weapons to accomplish his goals.

Named after the Italian poet Dante Alighieri, the character was designed to fit Devil May Cry game designer Hideki Kamiya's vision of a "cool and stylish" man, and his personality was based on the title character of the manga series Cobra. Dante's arsenal usually consists of firearms and melee weapons, including "Ebony and Ivory", twin handguns that never need reloading, as well as a variety of swords such as the "Rebellion" and "Force Edge", Devil Arms created by his father.

Dante has also become one of the most popular characters in gaming, having been recognized for his role in the Devil May Cry series and various characteristics that have attracted gamers. However, Dante's redesign and characterization in the reboot was the subject of controversy amongst gamers.
name: Dante

He serves as the protagonist of Assassin's Creed, Assassin's Creed: Altaïr's Chronicles and Assassin's Creed: Bloodlines. Altaïr also appears as a playable character in Assassin's Creed: Revelations and is playable once in Assassin's Creed II.

description:
The Skeleton King is a boss character found in Diablo 3, formerly known as King Leoric. Even though he was born in Kehjistan, Leoric decided to take his family and travel into the lands of Khanduras, where he in the name of the Zakarum, declared himself as the king. At first, the people of Khanduras disliked the idea to have him as a ruler. However, as time passed, they grew to like and respect him, thanks to his purity of heart and deed.

Unknown to Leoric however, his seat of power was the resting place of Diablo. He used the people too free himself from imprisonment, and took Leoric as his host for his evil deeds. Leoric tried to fight against it for a long time, but initially failed as Diablo stripped his soul from all honor and virtue. The people of Khanduras started to see a change in their king and how he became deformed and insane. He soon became cruel, and didn't hesitate to kill anyone or anything who dared to oppose him. Leoric even decided to execute Queen Asylla, his own wife. That's when he got the new nickname: "The Black King". 

One day, Leoric's lieutenant, the knight Lachdanan, came back from war, only to find his king mad and crazy, accusing people for kidnapping his son. Lachdanan begged for an explanation, but Leoric simply spat at him, calling him and his men traitors. With sadness in his heart, Lachdanen killed his king and Leoric cursed the knights just before his death.

King Leoric got a proper burial, but Diablo didn't want to give him that peace and raised him from the dead as a powerful undead warlord called the Skeleton King.
name: The Skeleton King

description:
Ratbag the Uruk craves power without knowing what he would do with it. He cannot heft a heavy weapon over his head, but he will, stupidly perhaps, attempt to claw his way to the top of Sauron's Army by aligning with his people's great enemy, the Gravewalker. 
 
He has deluded himself into believing the Ranger will help him become a Warchief and, once he has power, he will be able to keep all he has achieved. His many scars bear witness to his ineptitude and history of failure. He is a craven little thing whose only chance of success is in spite of himself.
name: Ratbag

description:
The Black Hand of Sauron is the greatest and most feared of the Black Captains. His mere presence spreads terror to all on the battlefield be it foe or servants alike. 
 
Some say he was once a king from the east who brought Sauron the heads of two Istari as gifts. Others say that he returned across the seas with Sauron after the fall of Númenor. Still others claim that he is the Dark Lord himself, taking fair form once again within Mordor. 
 
There are many stories of his origins. All of them are lies. The only things which are certain are that he is a master of deceit, and that he serves his Dark lord with absolute loyalty.
name: The Black Hand

description:
The Council consists of the group of 16 countries that created XCOM and who continue to fund and support the organization. The Council, represented by its mysterious shadowy spokesman, will make regular contact with the Commander (the player) via the Situation Room.

The Council has three primary reasons to contact XCOM:
Propose a new Council Mission, Present a special request from a member nation asking that XCOM supply them with certain items in exchange for a generous reward, and deliver the monthly report that evaluates and rewards the XCOM's actions.
name: Councilman
Liberty City Hardcore Drums and Vocals

description:
Albert Wesker is one of the central characters in the Resident Evil franchise by Capcom (or Biohazard in Japan). He was introduced in the original game and was the captain of U.S. police team STARS. Initially introduced as a supporting character in the first game, he has been one of the primary antagonists throughout the series, where he usually manipulates story events behind-the-scenes. 

He was a man who sought to replace the entire race through mass extinction and forced evolution, these thoughts causing Wesker to become very power-hungry. To this end, he was affiliated with the Umbrella Corporation as one of its most promising researchers, and at the same time participated in illicit activities by going undercover as S.T.A.R.S. captain in Raccoon City. After everyone found out about his betrayal, Wesker fakes his death and gains superhuman powers from an experimental variant of the Progenitor virus. He then starts working with Umbrella's mysterious rival company, TRICELL, until his defeat in Resident Evil 5.

Chris Redfield was the one who found out that Wesker worked for Umbrella, killing his plans. That's why he started to hate Chris, wanting nothing more than to destroy the guy. 
In terms of personality, Wesker was a cunning, deceptive, and highly intelligent bio-terrorist, usually preferring to observe the action from behind the scenes and then strike when the opportunity presented itself.
name: Albert Wesker

As the game progresses, increasing doubt is shed on Delilah, her relationship with Henry, her affiliation and what she potentially knows. As such, the player has the choice when making discoveries to report to her or not. The player never meets Delilah in person, leaving her appearance a mystery.

description:
If you play The Walking Dead: Season One by Telltale Games, you will meet Omid who is one of the many main characters. Omid is very friendly, kind-hearted and loving. He cares deeply for his girlfriend, Christa. Even though the world is going to hell, Omid has a positive view on life and tries to stay strong for others around him. He is often seen as the comic-relief of the group, and tries hard to lift the spirits of his companions. However he's not into heavy and troubling topics and tries to avoid it as much as possible. Additionally, Omid is assumed to be really intelligent, and is really into Civil War history. 

Before the zombie apocalypse, him and Christa shared an apartment in San Francisco. They owned a pet cat and enjoyed to travel. When the dead started to walk on the earth, they were on an "all American road trip". They went to Barstow, and had a Vegas Weekend together. Not much else is known about their past lives.

Christa and Omid later becomes Clementine's guardian & swears to protect her.
name: Omid

Her fun-loving nature has certainly managed to turn Mike's head - he dumped Emily in order to get with her.

A childhood ballerina, Jessica once wanted to be a cheerleader... until she realized that it was going be quite a lot of work.

description:
David Young is the main protagonist of D4: Dark Dreams Don't Die. He is a young beat private investigator who is highly trained in the forensic arts. Working as a police officer of the Boston Police Department's Narcotics Division, he soon met Peggy who he fell madly in love with. They got married and lived happily for a short period of time. Then one day, someone attacked Youngs' home, shot David in the head and Peggy's body was found drained of blood in the bathtub. Even though David somehow survived, the murder left him unable to recollect important memories. The only thing he remembers, was his wife's dying word to "look for D". This incident caused him to gain a time traveling ability. After finding out about it, mixed together with Peggy's murder case reaching a dead-end, he decided to quit the BPD to investigate the murder on his own. With the power, he uses mementos from past cases to try and solve the case by finding this mysterious "D".

David doesn't own a cellphone and collects records as a hobby.
name: David Young

description:
Elizabeth is a character and A.I. companion in BioShock Infinite.
With the game set in 1912 on a sky city (named Columbia) , Elizabeth is to take over the city once its current leader (or "Prophet"), Father Comstock, dies. Elizabeth can make and exploit "tears", rips to other universes, allowing her to move between them and/or bring in items from them. To prevent her from leaving Columbia, a remote "Siphon" is made which limits her powers, and she is locked in a tower under study and guarded by a giant mechanical bird known as Songbird.
name: Elizabeth

description: Ioreth is a character in Middle-earth: Shadow of Mordor and Talion's wife. She has a son named Dirhael and a father called Hallas.
name: Ioreth

description:
Talion is one of the two player-controlled protagonists in both Middle-earth: Shadow of Mordor and Middle-earth: Shadow of War, alongside Celebrimbor. However, they share the same body. 
 
A descendant of the Northmen in Rhovanion, and raised in Minas Tirith, he is a loyal Ranger of Gondor, where he then rose the rank of Captain of the Black Gate. After the tragic demise of his family and himself, Talion was revived by Celebrimbor, an immensely powerful Wraith; where the two joined forces and began a quest for vengeance on those responsible for the death of his loved ones the Black Hand of Sauron.
name: Talion

description:
Rigby is one of the protagonists of Carton Networks' Regular Show, as well as a playable character in the online game Fusion Fall. He's a 23 year old brown raccoon with short, spiky hair and made his debut in the pilot episode, working in the park as a groundskeeper. Rigby received the nickname "The One Cheek Wonder", after a friend damaged his butt in a "fun" fight. The raccoon had to get surgery that resulted in his behind looking like it only had one butt cheek.

Described as a "wild adult", he often becomes frightened, confused, frustrated or sad very easily. He can also be very impulsive, impatient and arrogant at times, his behavior causing him to act more like a child. Rigby cares a lot about his friends and tries to help the best he can.

Rigby is prone to overly dramatic reactions to the simplest things and often tries to skip work and disobey orders. However, as the series progressed, he has become a bit more responsible and thoughtful, tending to complain less and even accomplishing tough tasks.

He's terrified of horror movies.
name: Rigby

description: Captain David Edward Anderson is a human war hero and the original captain of the SSV Normandy. Anderson was born on June 8, 2137 to Ursula and Paul Anderson, a nurse and flight mechanic respectively, in the city of London on Earth, and was the last of three children by his parents' second marriage. Anderson is one of the Alliance's most decorated special forces operatives, and the first to graduate from the N7 marine program at Arcturus Station, serving with honor in the First Contact War.
name: David Anderson

description:
Ashley is a smart cookie. She's often found in the library, studying away with her nose in a book. 

After spending a lot of time with her study-partner Chris, Ashley wonders if he's interested in her as more than just a friend, but she soon snaps out of it - Chris would never ask her out anyway. 

Her overactive imagination means that she's jumpier than a paranoid kangaroo. She's not a fan of anything scary.
name: Ashley Brown

description: Admiral Daro'Xen vas Moreh is a member of the quarian Admiralty Board. She is known for her keen scientific interest in the geth.
name: Admiral Xen

description: Preston Garvey is a senior officer of the Commonwealth Minutemen, a volunteer defense militia operating in the Commonwealth in 2287. He is also available as a companion of the Sole Survivor.
name: Preston Garvey

description:
Noel Kreiss is a playable character of Final Fantasy XIII-2, and a supporting character in Lightning Returns: Final Fantasy XIII.

When Noel was born in the Farseer tribe (that lived a nomadic life), he was the second to last child. After the Cocoon came crashing down, it's crystal shattering, the event left the world in ruins and warfare broke out that killed the majority of mankind. 

When Noel travels back in time, he's the last remaining human being from 700 AF. He goes back to the past in order to try and change the outcome of his existence. He meets Lightning in Valhalla, who tells Noel about her sister and how she wants him to help them reunite while changing the future. Doing as he was told, he then goes to meet with Serah and quickly becomes her friend.

At first, Noel is cocky and confident, yet cheerful and soft-spoken. He's a self-sufficient fighter and a hunter that sadly suffers from amnesia thanks to the time paradox. Coming from a future where humanity is almost extinct, he has some trouble with his speech, so he tends to speak in a straightforward manner. The boy loves meeting new people and explore new places. Being very protective of others, he quickly starts caring for Serah and tries his best to protect her. Noel stands by his beliefs and morals, and as a remnant from his upbringing, values life and is reluctant to hurt or kill others unless necessary. This is the reason why he doesn't like Serah's boyfriend Snow, who has a very brash personality with the heads in the clouds.
name: Noel Kreiss

description:
Carley is one of the many main characters that appears in Telltale Games' The Walking Dead: Season One. She is a regional news reporter from Atlanta and a very skilled shooter. Carley's role is more active and she's never afraid to speak her mind. Having spent her time in war-zones as a correspondent, she presumably acquired basic knowledge of firearms and survival tactics that allows her to hold out during the outbreak.

Meeting Lee & Clementine in Macon, they later develop some kind of love relationship. Like the rest of the group, she cares about the members' welfare. Carley wants to save every survivor and give everyone a chance. Being very respectful and thoughtful, she reassures Lee that she will keep the secret to herself when he chooses to admit his past to her.

Not much is known about Carley's personal life, other than that she was raised Lutheran. The production crew drove to Macon to cover the Cherry Blossom Festival and that's when they were attacked by walkers. She was forced to watch her producer being eaten alive just a few feet away from her. Carley was saved by a guy called Doug.

Sadly, her life takes a turn for the worse as you get deeper into the story.
name: Carley

description:
Dr. Gordon Freeman is a fictional character and the main protagonist of the Half-Life video game series. 
 
His first appearance is in Half-Life. Gordon Freeman is an American man from Seattle, who graduated from MIT with a PhD in Theoretical Physics. He was an employee at Black Mesa Research Facility.
name: Gordon Freeman

description: Randy is an original character created by Telltale Games for Telltale Games' The Walking Dead: Season Two.
name: Randy

description: Faris NyanNyan (フェイリス・ニャンニャン), real name Rumiho Akiha (秋葉 留美穂), is a part-time employee and owner of the maid cafe May Queen Nyan-nyan, the same maid cafe that Mayuri works at, and is the most popular waitress there. She is a second year student in Kanaria Private Academy and is Yukitaka Akiha's daughter.
name: Faris Nyannyan

description:
Bwana is the main character in The Journey Down. He runs a gas station with his friend Kito in the shady corner of Kingsport Bay, at the outskirts of St Armando. They struggle hard to get costumers since the place is a bit run-down. The gas station, also known as Gas 'n' Charter, has been run by the guys ever since they were mysteriously abandoned by their adoptive father.

Little does Bwana know that he's about to be thrown into a emotional and spine-tingling adventure when he one day is approached by a mysterious woman from Agibo University called Lina. She is seeking a lost book that may hold the illegal secret to reaching the Underland. Bwana takes this as a chance to get out of the misery, and convinces Kito to come with them. Together they embark on this mysterious journey and Bwana hopes that he can finally uncover the true fate of their long lost father, Captain Kaonandodo.
name: Bwana

description:
Kate Beverly Marsh is one of the students at Blackwell Academy in the game Life is Strange. She is a nice and kind-hearted, rather shy teenager who doesn't like to be in the center of attention. She's also constantly bullied for her conservative views on sex and religion, and is a strong Christian. After someone records and uploads a video that goes viral because of uncharacteristic behavior (due to Kate getting drugged), Kate becomes very depressed and thinks that the spread of the video is a form of punishment to weaken her faith. Thanks to this event, she stops smiling and constantly looks worried and sad.

The main character of the game, Max, really likes Kate and makes sure to watch out for her during rough times. According to Max, Kate is beautiful and very friendly. They used to spend time together by going out on tea sessions, enjoying their friendship. After the event however, she stays in her dormitory and mostly sulks. She has a hard time doing artworks and stops playing the violin fully.

Kate was born into a heavily Christian conservative family. Her father Richard is a preacher in the Church. She has two younger sisters, one of them the 10-year-old Lynn Marsh. She doesn't drink alcohol and wages an abstinence campaign at her school.

She has a black and white pet bunny named Alice in her dorm room.
name: Kate Marsh

description: Every gun wielding, British, safari hunter, ever.
name: Sir Hammerlock

description:
Miranda Lawson is a human Cerberus Officer. As Jacob Taylor's informant, she gives him guidance and advice during missions, often via hologram. Miranda is very well traveled and has many contacts, extending from Citadel space and the Terminus Systems, to as far as the hostile Nemean Abyss. Her vast network of contacts may be explained by the fact Miranda is a known Cerberus operative, one who still has friends — or at least friends of friends — in the Alliance military. 
 
Miranda is a potential romantic interest for a male Commander Shepard.
name: Miranda Lawson
The President of the United States of America

description:
Victor Vran is the main character in the game Victor Vran. 
 
At the beginning of the game, Victor is travelling to the city of Zagoravia, destroyed and invaded by hordes of demons and undeads, in search of his friend Adrian, a fellow hunter, and Victor's best friend, the only one who knows his past. Despite being a member of Hunters Order, devoted to purge the world from demons and undead beings, Victor is not going to Zagoravia to answer the queen's call for help, as the city is overrunned by demons and many hunters had perished trying to oppose them, a disaster whose proportions are unprecedented.
name: Victor Vran

description:
Christa is a main character who first appears in Telltale Games's The Walking Dead: Season One, played by voice actress Mara Junot. She is much more serious than her boyfriend Omid, but loves him deeply and is concerned for the safety of the group. After Lee's death, Christa and Omid take up Lee's role as Clementine's guardians.

Little is known about Christa's life before the outbreak. She lived in a San Francisco apartment, and she and her boyfriend, Omid, were taking the "All-American Road Trip" when the apocalypse began...
name: Christa

description:
Exobiologist. Part of the Europa ground team in 'The Turing Test'. 
 
Birthplace: Damascus, Syria 
 
Nationality: Joint British & Syrian 
 
DOB: 2210 March 15th 
 
Sarah Brook's parents are both scientists. In her teenage years she was sent to an English public boarding school. 
 
Brook is one of the most eminent exobiologists of the 23rd century. For her formative work on the Mars Discovery Project, she was specially requested to be part of the Europa ground team. 
 
Though only 28 years old, Sarah has touched the surface of two planetoids and spent more time on alient soil than any other member of mankind (except the Mars team).
name: Dr. Sarah Brook

description: Yugo Tennouji (天王寺 裕吾) is Rintaro Okabe's landlord and the owner of the CRT store. He has a great passion for CRT Television and refuses to upgrade to any other type. This coupled with the fact he owns a CRT store has resulted in Rintaro nicknaming him "Mr. Braun" after the inventor of CRTs, German physicist Ferdinand Braun and the common Japanese name for CRTs, "Braun Tubes". His daughter Nae is his top priority and he will go to desperate lengths to ensure her safety.
name: Yugo Tennoji

description: Suzuha Amane (阿万音鈴羽) is a part-time employee for Yugo Tennoji, the landlord of Rintaro's flat and is on a search for her father in Akihabara. She enjoys riding her bicycle and appears to be at odds with Kurisu. She is the eight and last member of the Future Gadget Laboratory.
name: Suzuha Amane

description: Many a soldier of the Legion has disappeared on solitary watches when the Succubus is at large, lured in by her seductive calls. Swollen with stolen life, this daemon offers no true pleasure to those who succumb to her advances, but all the same her name carries a certain terrible allure.
name: High School Sweetheart

description: His past is not known but he is known to the public as an important government official and the Director of FEMA. He was appointed to FEMA through Page's manipulation of an unnamed senator infected with the Gray Death, and went to work immediately. A cloak-and-dagger man, Simons was the first higher-up on the scene after JC Denton's capture of NSF operatives in Battery Park; his interrogation ended with Simons personally executing both prisoners.
name: Walton Simons

description:
Matt is the high school's star linebacker, but he isn't necessarily the sharpest tool in the box. He's hoping for a sports scholarship to a top college, because his GPA isn't going to cut the mustard.

He mostly plays the part of the big friendly giant - but when Matt stays red, it's best to stay out of his way...

Matt is fiercely loyal to his girlfriend Emily... maybe even too loyal. Their relationship could be described as being a little one-way: when Emily says something, Matt does it.
name: Matthew Taylor

description:
Zinyak is an extraterrestrial warlord and the bad guy in Saint's Row IV. He's the leader of the alien race known as the Zin. Sounding very posh, he speaks with an upper class English accent and is a big fan of literature. It was actually the love for books that brought him to Earth. Zinyak often makes references from famous work, such as Macbeth and Edgar Allan Poe. 

During the events of the game, he invades Earth and comes through the ceiling of the White House where he abducts Kinzie Kensington and Shaundi before disappearing. He also defeats the Boss, who is now the President of the United States, and puts him/her into a virtual simulation based on their worst fears. 

Zinyak live streams everything to his planet where all the Zin can watch how he slowly but surely kills the humans and erases mankind. His goal is to take over, not really thinking that anyone on Earth can be strong enough to stop him.
name: Zinyak

description:
Lili Zanotto (from the game Psychonauts) is a 9 year old camper at Whispering Rock Psychic Summer Camp. Being the daughter of the Grand Psychonauts Chairman, Truman Zanotto, she is a gifted psychic, having passed all the tests and earned every merit badge they have. She's a big fan of plants och later develops feelings for the main character Raz. She starts calling him her boyfriend, which later becomes mutual.

She gets abducted by Linda the Lungfish and it's up to Raz to save her as Dr Loboto wants to extract her brain. Despite being Badass, she still needs rescue and it annoys her terribly.
name: Lili Zanotto

description: Nae Tennouji (天王寺 綯) is the only daughter of Yugo Tennouji and Tsuzuri Imamiya. She is a young girl living in fear of Rintarou Okabe and his Hououin Kyouma persona.
name: Nae Tennoji

description: PaRappa Rappa, alias Parappa the Rapper, is a paper-thin rapping dog and the main protagonist of the franchise Parappa the Rapper. His adventures usually lead to difficult situations which he counters with his catchphrase, "I gotta believe!", and pulls through.
name: PaRappa Rappa

description:
The main character of the Hyperdimension Neptunia franchise. She is the Console Patron Unit (CPU) of Planeptune. Neptune personifies a fictional Sega console, although her name was inspired by the Sega Neptune, which combined the Sega Genesis and 32X but was never released. 
 
Due to the Neptunia series being a game that revolves around different universes and dimensions, there are multiple Neptune's throughout the series though all of them retain more or less the same personalities and core aspects regardless of the setting.
name: Neptune

description:
Clementine, affectionately nicknamed Clem or Sweet Pea, is one of the main characters in the game The Walking Dead, by Telltale Games. She's not playable in season one, but the story still involves heavily around her. She is kind, polite and very mature for her age, acting as a moral compass of the group. Clementine is remarkably smart and good when it comes to improvising. She can be very practical during dire situations. She's more careful than other kids as she is aware of the current events going on. However, despite her maturity, Clementine is still relatively innocent in the way children are.

During the outbreak, Clementine ends up hiding in her tree-house after her babysitter goes missing, and her parents doesn't return home from vacation. A guy called Lee (the playable character) soon finds her and decides to take her with him after having to battle the babysitter who died and became a zombie. Together they embark on a long journey to find safety and eventually becomes very fond of each other.

After losing the people closest to her, Clementine becomes hardened and more mature in her outlook, but still bravely overcomes the dangers of a post-apocalyptic world head-on and tries her best to maintain some of her previous faith in humanity, hanging on to what Lee taught her and her own values.
name: Clementine

description: Mayuri Shiina (椎名 まゆり), is Rintaro Okabe's childhood friend and companion. She works part-time at a maid cafe called May Queen Nyan-nyan as a costume maid and occasionally makes cosplay outfits. She is also the second member of Rintaro's Future Gadget Laboratory. She is usually the one who financially supports Rintaro's "research" when food is needed. Although she possesses an extremely childish and naïve attitude for her age, she's also very attentive to details, often noticing things about people that others would miss.
name: Mayuri Shiina

description: A Plumber who saves the princess and defeats Bowser, his first appearance was in the 1981 game "Donkey Kong" as he is trying to save Pauline from the evil Donkey Kong, since the game grew in popularity, so did the plumber, until he got his own game in 1983. "Mario Bros." is a game where Mario and Luigi defeat creatures in the sewer, the game got positive reception, but Mario Bros. wasn't the game to improve Mario's popularity, and the game did not sell well in North America due to the Video Game Crash of 1983. Soon, Nintendo made what is known as one of the most iconic games of all time, "Super Mario Bros." , where Mario has to save Princess Toadstool from King Koopa. The game was a massive hit on the NES, selling about 40 million copies. They soon made more Mario games and now Mario is not only one of the best selling franchises but also one the most iconic video game characters ever.
name: Mario

description: Shiny Wasabi Kitty is a character that features on the Princess Robot Bubblegum series that featured in the HD Universe of the Grand Theft Auto series.
name: Shiny Wasabi Kitty - Princess Robot Bubblegum

description:
Chloe Frazer is an Indian-Australian treasure hunter and thief for hire; she's a skilled professional whose reputation often makes her highly demanded in the criminal underworld. She was also an associate, a major ally, and a former love interest to fellow treasure hunter Nathan Drake, and has also worked with other people such as Harry Flynn, Charlie Cutter, Nadine Ross, and Samuel Drake. 
 
Chloe was introduced in Uncharted 2: Among Thieves, serving as a central character and secondary love interest to Nathan Drake. She subsequently appears in Uncharted 3: Drake's Deception - in which she appears as a supporting character for the first act of the game, and is briefly mentioned in Uncharted 4: A Thief's End, before becoming the main protagonist of Uncharted: The Lost Legacy. 
 
In Among Thieves and Drake's Deception, Chloe was voiced and motion-captured by Claudia Black, who also recorded lines for the character in the multiplayer mode of A Thief's End. In The Lost Legacy, Claudia reprises her role as Chloe, while motion-capture was done by Michelle Lee.
name: Chloe Frazer

description:
A bit older than the rest of the group, Josh is something of an older brother figure to Chris. He loves taking the helm, organizing cool events and making sure everyone has an awesome time.

Josh definitely has a bit of a party-animal streak (honed in his freshman year), but his warm and friendly personality will win everybody around in the end.
name: Joshua Washington

description: Angio is an amateur singer who resembles a young Jezz Torrent (as he appeared in GTA Vice City) and even sings one of his solos. The Judges initially insult William after his performance with two of the judges voting it "Shame" but after Lazlow begs everyone to do something controversial to get ratings, Hugh Harrison votes William "fame" and the other judges follow suit despite already making their votes. Hugh then asks William to punch Lazlow, which he does twice.
name: William Angio - Fame or Shame

akas: ['Assistant', 'Celeb Sev', 'Celeb Seventeen', 'Christina', 'KuriGohan and Kamehameha', 'Mother of Time Machine', 'The Zombie']
description: Kurisu Makise is a genius girl who graduated from university at the age of seventeen. She is a research member in Victor Qondria University's Brain Research Program and her research on the brain's memory retention system has earned critical acclaim in the scientific community. She later joins the Future Gadget Lab as Member 004 after a series of encounters with Rintaro Okabe, where she helps to create the Time Leap Machine, a microwave oven capable of sending memories 48 hours back in time. She has a myriad of nicknames, most of which are invented by Rintaro, much to her dismay.
name: Kurisu Makise

description: Dr. Nakabachi (real name Shoichi Makise) is a scientist researching in the field of time-travelling.
name: Dr. Nakabachi

description:
Draven (from League of Legends) was never satisfied with victory in battle (unlike his brother, Darius). He wanted glory and recognition, seeking greatness in the Noxian military, However, they didn't appreciate his drama. Wanting to share "Draven" with the world, he turned his attention to the prison system. There, he turned the tedious affair of executions into a spectacle.

During the first execution, Draven shocked people when he forced the doomed prisoner to run for his life. Just before the successful escape, he brought the prisoner down with a throw of his mighty axe. Soon all of the Noxian prisoners raced for a final chance at life. Using this event as his own personal stage, he turned the killings into entertainment. Crowds flocked to see Draven in action, and tales of his performances spread quickly. As his popularity grew, so did his already-inflated ego. He just loved the center of attention. Before long, the scope of his ambitions outgrew the population of Noxus. That's when he decided that the entire would needed a dose of the glorious Draven.
name: Draven

description:
Dark Knight. Caped Crusader. World’s Greatest Detective. Whatever you know him as, wherever you know him from—the blockbuster movies, TV shows, video games, cartoons, or millions of comics—Batman is proof you don’t need superpowers to be a superhero… and the poster boy for what a bad childhood can do to you.

Millionaire Bruce Wayne was just a kid when he watched his parents get gunned down during a mugging in Gotham City. The crime would define his life, as he dedicated himself to becoming the world’s greatest weapon against crime—the Batman.

Forget his Batarangs, Batmobile, or Utility Belt filled with high-tech weapons. Batman is the most feared superhero of all, because he’s pushed himself to the absolute pinnacle of human achievement. He’s a brilliant detective who’s mastered fighting techniques the world’s barely heard of. An Olympic-caliber athlete with a plan for every occasion, Batman’s seemingly always five steps ahead of his foes. But in his crusade against injustice, two questions always loom: How far will he go to protect the innocent, and will he sacrifice his humanity along the way?
name: Batman

description:
Mojo Jojo is a super villian and the main antagonist of Cartoon Network's The Powerpuff Girls franchise, both in the TV series and video games. He was Professor Utonium's former lab assistant and pet, being pretty sweet. Now, he's the Powerpuff Girls' arch-nemesis, wanting to destroy them with all his might. The urge to crush Townsville and the need to conquer the world keeps him going, no matter what. Mojo (who is a very smart) spends a lot of time creating new weapons or large robots. He has high-vocabulary use and long-lasting sentences.

When the professor created the girls, the Chemical X also hit Jojo, which gave him a huge brain, so large that it ended up sticking out of his head. He also was given new emotions, such as envy and anger. Soon, he became hateful towards the professor who started to ignore him and care more about the girls. Since then he spends his life wanting revenge. At first, he was isolated for a great period of time, becoming a loner. 

Mojo is a chimpanzee, but is often called an "ape", which irritates him.

Being very cunning, he often manages to play with the Powerpuff girls's naivety. Sometimes Mojo actually manages to find their weaknesses and use it against the girls in battle. Despite being very dark-natured, he lives another life outside of seeking revenge. He enjoys buying food instead of stealing it. He also likes to build model ships and values the sense of honor.

During one incident, Mojo Jojo actually manages to defeat the girls by outsmarting them. He nearly destroyed the girls, but the police managed to catch him and he ended up in jail, even angrier than before.
name: Mojo Jojo

description: Dr. Marcus Marshall is the husband of Deanne Marshall and the father of the Empress: Daphne Marshall, voiced by Elric Timothy Atchison (Elric Atchison)
name: Dr. Marcus Marshall

description:
Rosabeth of Melfia is a character in Dark Souls II and can be found near Majula, as a petrified statue who blocks the door to the Shaded Woods. Rosabeth is a very gifted pyromancy student and praises her teacher, a famed sorcerer. Getting fascinated by his sorceries, she went after him as he embarked on a journey. They ended up getting separated and Rosabeth tried to find her way back to him as she was attacked by a Basilisk. She managed to close the gate, but not before the monster used it's breath on her, turning the girl into a stone statue.

Eventually, the Bearer of the Curse released from her petrified state. She then resumed her task of finding her teacher, although she also came to the conclusion that she might be more of a burden to him and decides to keep her distance.
name: Rosabeth of Melfia

akas: ['Noct', 'ノクティス・ルシス・チェラム', 'ノクト']
description:
Noctis Lucis Caelum, or "Noct" for short is the main character in Square Enix's Final Fantasy XV (originally a spin-off titled Final Fantasy Versus XIII). He's the crown prince of Lucis, the last kingdom in the world to possess a crystal. The rest was lost through a protracted cold war. He's the only son of King Regis Lucis Caelum CXIII of Lucis. 

As a result from a dear-death incident when he was younger, Noctis was gifted with the power to foresee the deaths of others. He's the only character who can summon monsters and also has the power to manipulate multiple weapons at once. In the story, these powers are passed down through the royal line of Lucis.

Noctis personality is different from Squall Leonhart and Cloud Strife. He's more realistic, and described as a young guy trying to look "cool", citing his drinking coffee despite disliking it. He's actually naturally shy, but hides it under a cold exterior (something his clothes friends can see). He actually has both heroic and villainous traits, becoming somewhat of an anti-hero.

Noctis and his allies must defend their country when the empire of Niflheim attacks Lucis and the other countries of the world to take control of the world's surviving crystal.
name: Noctis Lucis Caelum

description: Dr. Zed is the only human resident in Fyrestone to meet the Vault Hunters upon their arrival in Pandora. Dr. Zed lost his medical license for unknown reasons, probably something to do with the fact that he never had any medical training. Currently, he maintains the medical vendors around Pandora, more or less. He spends much of his time in the infirmary chopping up corpses.
name: Dr. Zed

description:
Joyce Price is the mother of Chloe Price in the game Life is Strange. She is the widow of William Price and a long-time resident of Arcadia Bay. She works at a local eatery called 'Two Whales Diner' and is an excellent cook. As a player, you get to meet her in the second episode of the game, "Out of Time".

In 2008, her husband William died in a car accident. Joyce often blames herself for the death since she called him and asked for a ride that resulted in his car crashing. Later on she met David Madsen while working at the diner and ended up marrying him. However, she still has a little place in her house that's like a shrine, dedicated to her former husband. Chloe isn't happy with the new relationship, as she feels that David Madsen tries to be a replacement for her father.

Joyce still lives in the same house from Chloe's childhood. As a mother, she is strong, loving and protective. She's very kind and hardworking, with a touch of sass. Even though Joyce and her daughter fights a lot. she wants what's best for Chloe, no matter what.
name: Joyce Price

description: Kasumi (means "haze" or "mist") Nakano (means "in the field") is a 19 year old human female that appears in the Fallout 4's add-on Far Harbor. You'll find her on the Island in 2287. She is curious, naive and gets easily bored. Kasumi and her grandfather had a large mechanical knowledge and started to restore pre-War appliances around her house together. After restoring a radio, she contacts DiMa, where she is led to believe that she is actually a synth. Odd dreams and her abilities also reinforces this belief. Later, Kasumi flees Acadia and it's her future is based on the player's choice.
name: Kasumi Nakano

description:
Commander Shepard is the player character in BioWare's Mass Effect game trilogy: Mass Effect, Mass Effect 2, and Mass Effect 3. A veteran soldier of the Systems Alliance Navy military and N7-graduate of the Interplanetary Combatives Training (ICT) program, and the first human Citadel Council Spectre, Shepard works to stop "the Reapers", a sentient synthetic-machine race dedicated to wiping out all organic life.

Shepard's gender, class, first name and general appearance are chosen and customised by the player. Mark Meer provides the voice for male Shepards, while Jennifer Hale voices females. Since the player can choose the gender of Shepard, much of the dialogue revolving around the character is gender neutral with only a few exceptions.

Alan Shepard was the source of the character's name. Shepard's armour developed over the series, and was originally intended to be red-and-white. Though both genders were given equal importance during development, marketing felt there was a need for a single identifiable hero for promotion of the game. Various merchandise has been made, including several figurines. Shepard has appeared in cameo appearances in other Electronic Arts games, though they will not be appearing in any future Mass Effect ones.
name: Commander Shepard (male)

description: Peach (or Princess Peach) is a main protagonist in the Mario series. She's usually the damsel-in-distress of the games, who the players have to rescue, but she also has some important roles as the hero herself. She's the adorable and cute princess of the Mushroom Kingdom.
name: Peach

description:
Emily has a quick tongue and a sharp wit. She's well-known within the group for her withering putdowns, but that does mean that she can come across as a bit of a bitch.

Always immaculately dressed, Emily prizes her appearance very highly. She believes that good taste is everything, and isn't afraid of dropping serious cash on clothes... and making sure that everyone knows about it.

Emily is currently dating Matt... but only because she's rebounding pretty hard after Mike dumped her a few weeks back.
name: Emily Davis

description: Powerful and well connected Leshin. Looking for her son, Folren, who is believed to have died during the war. Convinced he is either still alive or buried improperly, she hires Sofya to find out what really happened to him, but may have alternate motives for the investigation.
name: Tiatha ir-Adech

description:
GLaDOS (Genetic Lifeform and Disk Operating System) is the central core designed to control, guide, and oversee the Aperture Science computer-aided Enrichment Center. 
With the ability to shift and move facilities and various chambers, GLaDOS is able to achieve a seamless and almost infinite testing design whilst residing in the Central AI Chamber. 
 
She is the antagonist of Portal and the first half of Portal 2.
name: GlaDOS

description: Garrus Vakarian is a turian, formerly part of C-Sec's Investigation Division. Like most turians, Garrus had his military training at fifteen, but later followed in his father's footsteps to become a C-Sec officer. He was responsible for the investigation of Saren Arterius, the Council's top Spectre, after the Alliance claimed Saren had gone rogue. Although Garrus was told that the investigation was over, he decided to defy the Executor's order and pursue another lead on his own. Eventually, Garrus attempts to join Commander Shepard's team to help defeat Saren and the geth.
name: Garrus Vakarian

description:
Big-Foot/Sasquatch the names don't matter but the legend remains the same. Thought to be nothing more than superstition by Native's of the land; the Big-Foot is half man, half beast in the form of a hairy ape. 
 
The beast is rumored to have the strength of ten men and the ferocity of a grizzly bear, in Terrordrome the Sasquatch is neither friend nor foe, it simply wants to be left in peace but the chaos going on around it has caused it to awaken from it's slumber and take the fight back to the enemy.
name: Sasquatch

description:
Ursula is a 32 year old female Newman and a supporting character in Phantasy Star II & Phantasy Star Portable 2. Newmans are a race evolved from humans in the universe. They were created for research purposes, but eventually became a race of their own. She is a brilliant and sharp woman with many talents. She spent many years in the Alliance Military Force, where she met Kraz Muehler. They fell in love and decided to marry each other.

After being an instructor of AMF, she became a leader of Little Wing and her beauty mixed with her talents sent out a message of respect and dignity. Ursula however, often hides her feelings, leaving her with many regrets about her past. She's often sad about a lot of choices and thinks about them a lot. 

Ursula is also a fashion designer.
name: Ursula

description:
Trundle (League of Legends) is a devious troll with a mischievous streak. He can bend anyone to his will, as well as beat anyone and anything into submission. During a fight, he chills his enemies with his massive, frozen club and runs them through with shards of sharp ice. Trundle chases down anyone foolish enough to enter his domain and laughs as they bleed onto the tundra.

Trundle's warband once followed a weak leader, and were very foolish and cowardly. He feared that his kind would fall prey to other troll hordes. When he tried to win over the leader, but failing, he made up a story to fool others that if he found a weapon that would weird a great power, he would be the rightful leader of the warband. The trolls actually believed this story, but didn't think that he would succeed in his task.

Leaving the safety of his home, he went into the realm of the scary Ice Witch, hoping to find a weapon to prove his elaborate tale. Finally, he found his prize: a magical club of never-melting True Ice. Grabbing the weapon, the cold power run through him just as the Ice Witch appeared. Not wanting to die like this, she told the witch that she could use his troll army and that it would be a huge benefit for her.

Returning home, Trundle killed the leader after naming her weapon "Boneshiver" and took control of the warband. With Trundle leading the charge, the time of the trolls had finally come.
name: Trundle

description:
Commander Shepard is the player character in BioWare's Mass Effect game trilogy: Mass Effect, Mass Effect 2, and Mass Effect 3. A veteran soldier of the Systems Alliance Navy military and N7-graduate of the Interplanetary Combatives Training (ICT) program, and the first human Citadel Council Spectre, Shepard works to stop "the Reapers", a sentient synthetic-machine race dedicated to wiping out all organic life.

Shepard's gender, class, first name and general appearance are chosen and customized by the player. Since the player can choose the gender of Shepard, much of the dialogue revolving around the character is gender neutral with only a few exceptions.
name: Commander Shepard (female)

description:
This character is from TES 5 Skyrim mod called Bruma. 
 
A khadjit who lives in Bruma. Originally from Elsweyr Dar'taqto has lived most of his life in Cyrodil. He says that he moved from Elsweyr so long ago that does not rememder what the reason was. Maybe he just doens't want to tell the reason. 
 
Dar'taqto seems to have warm feelings towards Elsweyr. He can even tell the protagonist "You are to Dar'taqto as the sun is to Elsweyr... I mean - a good friend". 
He says that he would like to become emperor one day. It seems that he is dissapointed in current emperor. 
 
Dar'taqto gets banned from Bruma but the protagonist can help him by taking him along as follower. 
 
He fights enemies with two battle axes. Dar'taqto wears light armor. 
 
WARNING: The outfit on the picture is not his original outfit. The picture is taken at Skaal Village, Soltheim.
name: Dar'taqto

description: Booker DeWitt (Troy Baker), the player protagonist, is a disgraced former agent of the Pinkerton National Detective Agency. As a soldier in the 7th Cavalry Regiment, he had performed brutal acts against native American Indians at the Battle of Wounded Knee to defend his own honor; these acts left him emotionally scarred, leading to excessive drinking and gambling and earned him the title "White Injun" due to his tendency to scalp those he killed. He was given an opportunity to be baptised and start anew, but ultimately declined. He was subsequently dismissed for behavior beyond the acceptable bounds of the Agency,[2] but considers his actions with the Pinkertons in quelling labour strikes to be among his many sins. He continues to work as a private investigator from New York City, referring to himself as an "independent contractor". Outwardly, he cares little for the extraordinary, provided that it does not interfere with his ability to do his job; internally, he is disturbed by both his role in the events at Wounded Knee and recurring visions of New York City under attack from the air. Booker is skeptical of faith, unwilling to accept the idea that he can be absolved of his sins by embracing religion, as he considers his sins to be so extreme as to demand a penance rather than forgiveness.
name: Booker DeWitt
Malady / Betty / Henny / Skeletal Cat / Outhouse / Mummie Dearest / various NPCs

description:
Following yet another disappearance in a series of strange events in the isolated rural town of Staten, private detective Jack Norwood decides to take matters into his own hands and find out who, or what, is behind the mystery. 
In 'The Missing Few', you play as Jack Norwood, a private detective who goes to the seeks to unravel the mystery of the disappearances in Staten. 
 
The character will go through many changes throughout the game and it's up to the player to decide the future of Jack.
name: Jack Norwood

description:
Karma (League of Legends) is a strong leader torn between tradition and revolution. She's the soul of Ionia made manifest and wants nothing more than to protect the peace, even if it's by force. Karma is an inspiring presence on the battlefield, turning back her foes and shielding her allies. Her spiritual power and strong will makes her a dangerous opponent. 

Before the fight, she lived a peaceful life in a small village. Led by elder monks, the villagers practiced a tradition of benevolent magic and pacifism. Karma became a beloved mediator and embraced the tradition. When the Noxus armies invaded Ionia, the elder monks insisted on talking to the general and make peace right away, a plan that Karma didn't agree upon as she had heard stories of Noxian cruelty. She ended up being right as the monks were slaughtered and soldiers ordered to strike the village.

Karma would not accept death as an outcome and sacrificed herself by drawing out the power within to summon the full force of her will. The flame took the form of twin dragons who won against the army. When the magical finally disappeared, Karma found out that the general had fallen before her.

She then became the leader of the Ionian resistance, but that didn't stop the problems. Ionia became divided between fighters who wanted revenge, and the monks who demanded the return of a spiritual tradition. Karma stood in the middle, wanting a third way. She now seeks to return her ravaged land to an enduring peace.
name: Karma the Enlightened One
Ambulance / Snow Plough / Police Car / Sports Car

description:
Grand Arch Master of the Order of One. 
 
Dupoint Lucroix is the Grand Master trying to keep order while his assistant Alexander seeks to use the evils of mankind to better himself.
name: Grand Master Dupoint Lucroix

description: Hawke is the player-controlled protagonist of Dragon Age. Hawke is fully voiced, can be either male or female and has a fully customizable appearance.
name: Hawke (male)

description: Alyx Vance is the deuteragonist of Half-Life 2 and its Episodes. She is portrayed as a woman in her mid-twenties, and is a prominent figure in the Resistance campaign against the rule of the Combine.
name: Alyx Vance

description:
Mr. Satan, also known as Hercule, is the World Martial Arts Champion and the Earth's protector in the Dragon Ball Z animation and video games. His real name is actually Mark. When Mark was young, he attended a fighting dojo called "Satan Castle." Through a combination of considerable power and good luck, he quickly became world champion and was called "Mr. Satan" after the name of his dojo. During the Dragon Ball X time period, Mr. Satan won the champion title by beating normal earthlings in a time when Goku and the other fighters were battling on Namek. He was already famous and rich, which resulted in him also being a egomaniac. On television he kept talking big about his strength and that he was the best fighter in the world.

Using his fame as "the Hero who defeated Cell", he seduces and sleeps with girls, acting like a leech who always turns his head when seeing a pretty face. He is very protective of his daughter Videl however, and would not allow her to hang out at any boy's house unless they are tougher than him.

If you dig deeper down in Mark's personality, he's actually a decent and honorable man with a kind heart. He genuinely cares about protecting the innocent and fighting for justice the best as he can. He shows moments of great courage when his family and friends are threatened by evil.
name: Mr. Satan

description:
Hel is a Goddess and the keeper of the dead, lying judgement on souls to decide to is reborn. Beautiful and terrible she has both sides of two extremes. She's the daughter of the trickster God, Loki which means that her destiny was pretty much doomed to darkness from the very start. All-Father Odin had a prophecy that Hel and her siblings would end up creating Ragnarök, the battle that would end everything.  Wanting to prevent this, he cast them all into different realms and Hel got to rule over the realm of dead. 

When she was born, her face was cast half in light, half in shadow, meaning that she was both dead and alive at the same time. As the spirits of the kind-hearted, the sick, the elderly were brought to her, she cared for them, gave them comfort, yet those she deemed evil she mercilessly hurled into the frozen depths of Niflheim. 

One day, Hel will fulfill her prophecy, though it's still unknown if she will be a shadow of darkness or a force of light.
name: Hel

description:
Zenyatta is an omnic robot monk who travels around the world in search of spiritual enlightenment. It's said that those who cross his path are never the same again. He's an offensive support hero that can cripple enemies and help allies. He has low health and mobility, but his Transcendence makes him briefly invulnerable. Zenyatta also calls upon orbs of harmony and discord to heal or hurt others.

A former member of the Shambali, Zenyatta didn't like the group's approach. Believing that forming people into relationship can heal the world, he eventually left and took his own path. While coming across others, he stayed to help them overcome their personal struggles to find inner peace.

At some point, he encountered Genji who had at the time left Overwatch. He was very conflicted with his nature as a cyborg and Zenyatta later became his mentor. Under the monk's tutelage, Genji reconciled his dual existence as both man and machine and Zenyatta saw Genji as one of his brightest pupils.
name: Zenyatta

description:
Takumi, a very talented archer, is a major playable character from Fire Emblem Fates. He is the third child of four in the Hoshidan royal family. Takumi has been perfecting his practice of martial arts in order to have people recognize him for his strength. Starting out with a sword, he was actually pretty good. Sadly he was humiliatingly crushed by Ryoma during a match  that caused him to become an archer instead. 

Takumi can be very moody due to developing a bit of an inferiority complex. His desire to become someone big is so strong, and he want to do it on his own, without people comparing him to his siblings. This obsession becomes both a strength and a flaw. Mentally though, Takumi is rather weak. He is also a very cautious person and can easily be suspicious of new people around him. People who gained Takumi's trust, are some of the few that gets to see and appreciate his friendly side.

Out of everyone in the army, he is the one who gets the worst dreams.
Takumi has an interest in shogi and loves miso soup.

At the end of Chapter 6, depending on the side the Avatar chooses, Takumi's involvement in the plot will be altered.
name: Takumi

description:
The G-Man is a mysterious and enigmatic character encountered several times in the Half-Life series. Referred to as a "sinister interdimensional bureaucrat",[3] he is known to display peculiar behavior and to wield powers far beyond those of a human. His identity and motives remain completely unexplained. His allegiance also remains unknown to this day. 
He plays the role of an overseer and eventual employer, watching over Gordon Freeman and other characters as the series progresses, at times helping or hindering them.
name: G-Man

description:
"Life is complicated. I never thought I would live like this. I killed people, smuggled people, sold people... Perhaps here, things will be different." - Niko Belic

Niko Belic is the lead character in Grand Theft Auto IV.
name: Niko Bellic

description:
Nature-loving Sam is a warm and caring individual. The others might find her a little quirky, but she's comfortable in her own skin.

She is strong willed and doesn't scare easily.

The weekend away is a chance for Sam to catch up with friends, enjoy the mountain air and put the past behind her.
name: Samantha Giddings
'Eight Stories from Mousewood' Audio Stories read by

description:
Agent 47 is the main character from the Hitman series and a highly skilled assassin, both in ability and in his techniques. He's a relatively emotionless assassin, but can now and then show some signs of morality, like when confessing his sins to Father Vittorio. Agent 47 doesn't work to gain money, but to have a purpose in life.

He is emotionally closed off to the suffering of others when appropriate on a contract, even if they remind him of himself at a younger age. His absolute highest priority is completing his contract. He will sacrifice innocents if he must, but he will kill the target. Vocally, he rarely raises his voice, choosing to speak in a calm and relaxed manner at all time. When speaking to another person, he can perfectly mask his true intentions and fool the other party with no effort. Agent 47 approaches his assassinations with professionalism but will, however, not show any hesitation or remorse when it comes to killing or silencing witnesses and other potential threats to his mission. 

His genetically engineered mind and body make competition next to nothing, and for this reason, Agent 47 is considered to be the world's most greatest assassin.
name: Hitman

description: Adkarna Valkyrie (Heroes of Newerth) is a special skin to the Hero Valkyrie. The ancient sagas of the heathen north have long told to the tale of the battle-women known as Valkyries. For centuries, their ranks have thinned as the old ways have died out and civilization stretched its smothering hand over the frozen wilds. But some Valkyries still remain, cold and swift as the north wind, wielding their lances with expertise to rival the most veteran Legion warriors.
name: Adkarna Valkyrie

description:
Chie Satonaka comes from Persona 4 and is a playable character. Being one of the protagonist's classmates at Yasogami High School, Chie is a very energetic and outgoing girl who likes to dress up as a tomboy. She always try to be bright and upbeat, and by joking about the case as much as possible, she feels that she can cheer up the group. Obsessed with Kung Fu (having a Bruce Lee poster in her room), she's a big fan of martial arts movies, 'Trial of the Dragon' being her favorite. Depending on who she hangs out with, she can somewhat be very short tempered and is slow to back down from a challenge.

The biggest insecurity Chie has is her femininity. Even though she's a bit jealous of Yukiko and the attention boys gives her, Chie's somewhat harsh personality makes it hard for boys to approach her on a romantic level. There are, however, some boys that secretly finds her very cute and cool. As a result she comes to believe herself to be undesirable.

Later on, by the end of the game and anime, she acknowledges her own strengths and ends up becoming comfortable with her own feminine side.

Chie is afraid of thunder (it causes panic attacks) and ghost stories.
name: Chie Satonaka
Eranir, Viscount Marcius Carvain, Additional Voices

description:
As The Tower's evil has grown, so has his stature. He is trapped inside armor that will not grow with him, and his agony is exquisite. He was once a Númenórean and as he can recall, he either built a tower, or was locked inside one. 
 
His appearance is horrific. To stand near him is to feel the revulsion he feels for himself. Even his fellow Captains despise The Tower, although they have come to rely on his great corrupting evil. His propensity for slaughter is unmatched. He makes his victims feel his pain, and he revels in it.
name: The Tower

description:
Snow White is a character from the game The Wolf Among Us, as well as the comic Fables. She serves as the Assistant to the Deputy Mayor of Fabletown, Ichabod Crane (during King Cole's absence). She got this job thanks to her experiences from her days in the Homelands. Snow White married Prince Charming after escaping imprisonment, but eventually found out that he was cheating with Rose Red, Snow White's sister. Now she spends her days trying her best to keep Fabletown a safe haven for the Fables in the New World living among the Mundies, aka the humans.

Her character is based on the story of the same name. Snow is a close personal friend of Bigby Wolf, the town's sheriff. She is often blamed by Ichabod Crane by mistakes she didn't do (including stealing a bottle of his finest wine) and fears that the future of the Fables are going downhill, that it's not looking bright at all.

One day Snow White awakens Bigby and alerts him of a murder. She joins the investigation and uses the Book of Fables and the Magic Mirror in order to find out more clues about the victim.

Thanks to her attitude, many describes her as being an "ice queen". After the divorce, Snow became independent and cold. However, she doesn't lack the role to be a leader, and can be very charismatic at times. She actually does have a compassionate heart and displays a kind-hearted attitude towards children. Having a strong belief in justice, she worries and wants to help the less fortunate Fables.
name: Snow White

description:
Eddy Raja is a character from the Uncharted franchise. He's the leader of an Indonesian pirate gang and a treasure hunter. A long time ago, Eddy was actually Nathan Drake's "best friend". They then worked together in a hunt to find the Eye of Indra. Later, when becoming interested in El Dorado, the gang teamed up with Gabrial Roman and Atoq Navarro in order to find the treasure before Nathan and his gang.

With a dad that's a crime lord, Eddy Raja is loud and egoistic, always talking about the treasures he discovered. He's also well-known for addressing himself in third-person, having a quick temper and using childish catchphrases. Moral isn't important as he works for the side that pays him best. Some people sees him as incompetent and stupid as Nathan keeps tricking him over and over. Gamers however, seems to enjoy his witty comics as he becomes a form of comic relief in dire moments.

Despite having a mostly negative personality, Eddy cares a lot about his pirate crew, as well as his sister. He shows great concern for his friends when they one after another gets killed by an unknown force.

Eddy Raja, like most other villains in the series, is known for double-crossing people when it comes to treasure hunting.
name: Eddy Raja

description:
If you play Dying Light, you will encounter a character called Karim. He's one of the two sub-leaders of Rais' gang. At first, Karim doubts the main character Crane, thinking that he's not going to be able to keep his promises. Later on, however, as Karim and Crane works together, he becomes a bit attached to Crane.

Karim was a former bodyguard for Erol Asani. During the outbreak, Asani gets bitten by a zombie in the leg. In haste to save Asani's life as his bodyguard, Karim amputates the leg, ignoring the fact that Asani didn't want that to happen. Karim gets fired and forced to leave on his own.

While working with Crane, Karim mentions that he might have stolen some supplies for himself at the airdrop. But out of respect for his new friend, he ends up leaving the stuff to instead be collected by the player.

Later on, Rais betrays everyone and shoots Karim who gets fatally wounded. About to die he tells the main character that this was his punishment for trying to work with Rais. He also warns Crane that Rais has trapped the house nearby with explosives and that he needs to get away. Then, sadly, he finally succumbs to his wounds.
name: Karim

description:
Francis York Morgan is an FBI special agent, and the main character of Swery65's game, Deadly Premonition. Even though he solves cases in a very peculiar way, he's a very competent agent with a real talent for criminal profiling. His personality differs from normal humans with his odd mannerisms and weird morning routines (like drinking his strong morning coffee and seeing secret messages in each cup). Francis York Morgan also urges people to call him York, because that's what "everyone does".

He has a tendency to talk to a character known as Zach, someone whose existence is a mystery to him and others. Yet he follows Zach's advice, no matter what it might be.

When the story of Deadly Premonition begins, York is in the small town Greenvale. They called him there to investigate the murder of a young woman. York thinks that it might be connected to older murder investigations that he worked on, and is determined to do whatever it takes to find the last puzzle pieces and end the nightmare.
name: Francis York Morgan
Sebastian - Kung Fu Rainbow Lazer Force

description: Luka Urushibara (漆原るか) is a close friend of Mayuri Shiina and so-called protégé of Rintaro Okabe. While feminine in appearance and personality, Luka is a male. Mayuri is his classmate, who often attempts to coerce him into cosplaying (without much success).
name: Luka Urushibara

description:
Neo Periwinkle Cortex has a professionally evil mind and is the villain of the Crash Bandicoot series. He also goes by Doctor Neo Cortex, N, Cortex or Doctor Cortex. Born in Peoria, he's known to create his nemesis: Crash Bandicoot. The doctor embodies many classic traits of of psychopathy and is very short-tempered. He tries frequently to manipulate others to get what he wants.

Like many other bad guys, Cortex holds a grudge against other scientists for ridiculing his outlandish ideas. That's why he is determined to take over the world in order to prove them wrong. Later however, he ends up working for Uka Uka who is one of the only two individuals that Cortex fears. Although he talks big and thinks he's better than others, he's usually nervous in the face of immediate danger. The doctor also relies a bit too much on his minion Tiny TIger to end Crash, as he fails almost constantly. For most of the time, Cortex doesn't care for the lives and feelings of others, caring only for himself and what he wants. 

Other bad traits of the villain is that he can become very agitated if things don't go his way. He's not above lying and often deceives others to fulfill his evil desires.

In almost all games, Cortex is usually the final boss.
name: Dr. Neo Cortex

description:
Beowulf is a character from Skullgirls and a hot-blooded wrestler. He really enjoys the spotlight he received from wrestling. A character called Cerebella is noted as being a huge fan of him. In official artwork of Beowulf, Cerebella is seen eagerly getting his autograph. 

Even after his downfall following the defeat of Grendel and the slaying of his mother, he is unwilling to give up his career and wants to please his fans. He's not really known for thinking about things beforehand as he was focusing on the career while receiving advice from his "manager" Zane, who is a very shady character, rather then focusing on the real problem.

Even though Beowulf has his sides, he's actually somewhat of a talented fight and a good person who really cares for his fans and other people. Known world-wide for felling the Gigan warrior Grendel and for his illustrious career in the ring, Beowulf had secured himself a spot in the history books as a champion. 

Now, as the Canopy Kingdom faces a new threat, Beowulf enters the ring again , hoping for yet another glorious victory.
name: Beowulf
Bentior, Gort, Retching Cornelius, Additional Voices

description: Rintarou Okabe (岡部 倫太郁) is a self-proclaimed mad scientist and the main protagonist of Steins;Gate. He is a student of Tokyo Electronics University and the founder of Future Gadget Laboratory, a small research laboratory devoted into creation of future gadgets for the betterment of mankind. He also likes to pose as an agent working against a certain "Organization" which he thinks is always after him, as he believes this kind of image gives him a cool and mysterious aura. He is one of the (accidental) inventors of the Future Gadget #8, Phone Microwave, which has the ability to send data back in time.
name: Rintaro Okabe

description:
In Telltale Games' The Walking Dead, there's many main characters and one of them is Kenny. As a kid he was raised by his father, who taught him how to repair broken cars. That knowledge soon extended to boats due to his love of the water and traveling. As an adult, Kenny became a commercial fisherman, hunting for the snapper fish and yellow fin. During a fishing trip, he found a sick octopus and decided to bring it to a veterinarian's office. There he met and fell in love with Katjaa. They got married and later had a son called Kenny Jr, also nicknamed Duck. The family were returning from Memphis, Tennessee after visiting Katjaa's sister when the outbreak started.

Meeting Lee and Clementine along the way, they decided to stick together for a better chance of survival. Kenny acted as a co-leader of Lee's group (but eventually acknowledged Lee as the true leader) but his short temper and failure to think things through often got the better of him. However, Kenny is also shown to be selfless and kind, being willing to give his life to save someone else's. 

Kenny often went sailing to the open sea for months at a time, separated from his family, which he admits to be a fact that he deeply regrets after his son gets bitten by a zombie and his wife commits suicide because of the loss of Duck.

Kenny displays numerous stereotypes of a redneck and suffers from insomnia.
name: Kenny

description: Moeka Kiryu (桐生萌郁) is a part-time editor whom Rintaro Okabe encounters in Akiba. She is practically glued to her phone and cannot function without it. Even when face to face, Moeka prefers to communicate by email.
name: Moeka Kiryu

description:
In the game, Sea of Lies: Leviathan Reef, you meet the dastardly Pirate King. He is out for blood and quickly picks you as his next target. To get revenge against the player's father, the infamous pirate has a plan involving kidnapping and hurting you. Instead of looking for you himself, he sends another captain who instead of kidnapping the player, lets them go. During the game, you have to find your way out of a mysterious island full of pirates, with no one to trust. The only way to stop the King of Pirates is by finding a way to stop the villain for good.

The name of the pirate is Bartholomew.
name: The Pirate King

description:
Piers Nivans was a new character who appeared as a support member to Chris Redfield in the game Resident Evil 6. He was a combat operative for the North American Branch of the BSAA, assigned to the Special Operations Unit. According to his file, Piers' family has a great history in the military dating back to his great-grandfather. This made Piers want to follow this tradition and graduated at the top of his class from an elite military academy.

At some point, Nivans felt like he needed a greater challenge and met Chris Redfield who was very impressed with his skills as a sniper. Hearing that, he eventually became a member of Alpha Team as Chris' second-in-command.

During various missions, he managed to meet other well known characters such as Rebecca Chambers, Jake Muller and Sherry Birkin. Alpha Team also got in contact with Ada Wong.

Being the young ace of the BSAA, he was a naturally gifted marksman, much like his squad leader. Due to his extreme sharpness and concentration, he was known as "the man who never misses a target". He is characterized as an individual with a strong sense of responsibility and an astute discernment, being able to influence his teammates into the correct course in the battlefield. 

During a tragic meeting with a deadly B.O.W. named Haos, he attacked Piers, destroying his arm by crushing it. In order to save his commander, he infected himself with a virus, right into the wound. That gave him the capability to release massive quantities of bio-electricity through the prongs. After defeating Haos, they rush to the escape pods. However, Piers refuses to follow Chris, pushes him into the pod and ejects it. Chris leaves for the shore, forced to see his friend die.
name: Piers Nivans
